24:38.777 --> 24:44.750 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Many presidents of HBCUs are in
Washington
this week, calling for $25
billion more in

24:44.783 --> 24:46.552 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the upcoming budget.

24:46.585 --> 24:52.024 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HBCUs were established after the
Civil War
to provide higher learning for
black citizens

24:52.057 --> 24:55.060 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
who were deliberately shut out
of most universities.

24:55.094 --> 24:58.230 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Today, there are 100 HBCUS.

24:58.263 --> 25:01.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Nearly 300,000 students are
enrolled in them.

25:01.567 --> 25:05.637 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Every president since Mr. Jimmy
Carter has
issued executive orders on
HBCUS.

25:05.671 --> 25:11.677 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
During President Obama's tenure,
he expanded
Pell Grants for schools overall,
but initially

25:11.710 --> 25:16.315 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
