for black
colleges and never held meetings
with the

25:16.348 --> 25:17.316 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
group.

25:17.349 --> 25:18.951 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It was often a rocky
relationship.

25:18.984 --> 25:23.655 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
A number of HBCUs still are in
financial distress.

25:23.689 --> 25:28.427 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Johnny Taylor, president and CEO
of Thurgood
Marshall College Fund, which
helps fund HBCUs,

25:28.460 --> 25:30.629 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
